15/07/2004
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- A ceremony marking the official opening of the BiH State Investigation and Security Agency (SIPA) headquarters in Sarajevo took place Wednesday (14 July). Senior representatives of the international community and BiH authorities attended the event. In his remarks, High Representative Paddy Ashdown welcomed the creation of conditions making it possible for SIPA to work efficiently, saying this was a major step towards protection of BiH citizens on the road to Euro-Atlantic integration. The head of SIPA, Sredoje Novic, confirmed the institution's readiness to act decisively in the fight against organised crime, terrorism and money laundering. (PBS BiH, NTV Hayat, Fena - 14/07/04)
